{{Quote|I am saving you the trouble of embarrassing yourself with all the ''meesa meesa'' bantha poodoo. Just don't.|Aro N'cookaala, to [[Han Solo]]|<ref name="Last Shot">''[[Last Shot]]''</ref>}}
'''Gunganese''',<ref name="Aliens of the Galaxy" /> also known as '''Gungan'''<ref name="NoP">''[[Nexus of Power]]''</ref> or '''Old Gungan''',<ref name="Raiders of the Lost Gundark">{{IDWAdventuresCite-2017|issue=18|story=Raiders of the Lost Gundark}}</ref> was the native [[language]] of the [[Gungan]]s, an [[Amphibian|amphibious]] [[species]] from [[Naboo]]. In practice, the Gungans often used a pidgin tongue that combined [[Galactic Basic Standard]] with Gunganese words and speech patterns.<ref name="Aliens of the Galaxy" /> Although stereotyped as exclusively using the pidgin,<ref name="Last Shot" /> [[Unidentified Gungan dialect|Gungan-Basic dialect]],<ref name="Episode I">{{Film|I}}</ref> some Gungans, like [[Aro N'cookaala]], spoke perfect Basic.<ref name="Last Shot" />

==Examples==
{{Quote|There be some bombad clankens coming this way.''"<br />"''Yeah&mdash; What? Bombad clankens?|[[Jar Jar Binks]] and [[Clone Commander]] [[Stone (clone trooper)|Stone]]|<ref name="The Gungan General">{{TCW|The Gungan General}}</ref>}}
*''Heyo Dalee'' ("Hello")<ref name="SWTVE">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''</ref>
*''Mackineek'' ("[[Droid]]")<ref name="On the Front Lines">''[[Star Wars: On the Front Lines]]''</ref>
*''Flasher'' (''[[Blaster]]'')<ref name="On the Front Lines" />

==Behind the scenes==
In [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] sources, the term "Gunganese" was applied to the [[Gungan (language)|Gungan-accented pidgin Basic]] rather than the native Gungan language, which in turn was referred to as "[[Gunganese/Legends|Old Gungan]]."<ref name="Galactic Phrase Book and Travel Guide">[[Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide (real-life book)|''Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide'']]</ref>

